# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HassarPath | Scene: JaeidPath3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke the next day to the first beams of light cutting through the window."
    new "Sarah woke the next day to the first beams of light cutting through the window."

    old "From moon to sun."
    new "From moon to sun."

    old "It was nice that some things never changed, no matter where you were in the world."
    new "It was nice that some things never changed, no matter where you were in the world."

    old "Early up, the house was still rather quiet."
    new "Early up, the house was still rather quiet."

    old "Just outside, Sarah could hear the faint murmurs of the city coming to life."
    new "Just outside, Sarah could hear the faint murmurs of the city coming to life."

    old "She made her way towards one of the windows."
    new "She made her way towards one of the windows."

    old "With trembling fingers, she grasped the curtain and pulled it slightly to the side."
    new "With trembling fingers, she grasped the curtain and pulled it slightly to the side."

    old "Only just enough to see the world outside."
    new "Only just enough to see the world outside."

    old "Already, there were people about. Carts full of goods being stalled out."
    new "Already, there were people about. Carts full of goods being stalled out."

    old "Sarah didn't know much of the city yet, but she understood enough to suspect this was somewhat of a market district."
    new "Sarah didn't know much of the city yet, but she understood enough to suspect this was somewhat of a market district."

    old "Across the street, a vendor was putting out wares."
    new "Across the street, a vendor was putting out wares."

    old "Shining metals of gold, copper and silver. Glittering among them, gemstones."
    new "Shining metals of gold, copper and silver. Glittering among them, gemstones."

    old "A stall over, fabrics of silk that seemed to flow like milk."
    new "A stall over, fabrics of silk that seemed to flow like milk."

    old "There was an abudance here that Sarah had not expected."
    new "There was an abudance here that Sarah had not expected."

    old "Suddenly, one of the men on the street turned and made eye contact with her."
    new "Suddenly, one of the men on the street turned and made eye contact with her."

    old "Sarah felt her heart skip a beat."
    new "Sarah felt her heart skip a beat."

    old "Her breath was rapid and she placed her hand over her mouth, hoping to be quiet."
    new "Her breath was rapid and she placed her hand over her mouth, hoping to be quiet."

    old "You really should be careful."
    new "You really should be careful."

    old "Sarah turned and saw Jasmine standing on the opposite side of the room."
    new "Sarah turned and saw Jasmine standing on the opposite side of the room."

    old "I'm sorry, I was just..."
    new "I'm sorry, I was just..."

    old "Maybe Jaeid gave you the wrong impression when he claimed you, but this city is not as safe as you may be used to."
    new "Maybe Jaeid gave you the wrong impression when he claimed you, but this city is not as safe as you may be used to."

    old "He said he didn't claim me."
    new "He said he didn't claim me."

    old "Jaeid can say a lot of things. He doesn't always live in the real world."
    new "Jaeid can say a lot of things. He doesn't always live in the real world."

    old "I mean that this place...this is the capital of the Tribes."
    new "I mean that this place...this is the capital of the Tribes."

    old "Their culture rules every part of it. If you walk around here thinking you're still in Rosanna, things won't end well for you."
    new "Their culture rules every part of it. If you walk around here thinking you're still in Rosanna, things won't end well for you."

    old "And Jaeid might have saved you, but he isn't Khan."
    new "And Jaeid might have saved you, but he isn't Khan."

    old "When he says he won't treat you like a slave, that's what that means. He, and he alone, won't treat you like one."
    new "When he says he won't treat you like a slave, that's what that means. He, and he alone, won't treat you like one."

    old "Jasmine gestured towards the window. The world outside."
    new "Jasmine gestured towards the window. The world outside."

    old "Out there, no matter what Jaeid says, you are a slave. Property. A prize won."
    new "Out there, no matter what Jaeid says, you are a slave. Property. A prize won."

    old "If you forget that, you invite only danger."
    new "If you forget that, you invite only danger."

    old "So I am still a slave..."
    new "So I am still a slave..."

    old "Not within these walls. But the second you step outside, that is what you are."
    new "Not within these walls. But the second you step outside, that is what you are."

    old "So it's dangerous for me to go outside?"
    new "So it's dangerous for me to go outside?"

    old "Like I said, this place has its own culture. Its own rules. If you learn them, you'll do fine."
    new "Like I said, this place has its own culture. Its own rules. If you learn them, you'll do fine."

    old "Rules like what?"
    new "Rules like what?"

    old "Well, take for example when Jaied brought you here."
    new "Well, take for example when Jaied brought you here."

    old "Did you notice how nobody did anything to you? How you walked around safe wearing just about nothing?"
    new "Did you notice how nobody did anything to you? How you walked around safe wearing just about nothing?"

    old "Why do you think that is? Because they value women around here?"
    new "Why do you think that is? Because they value women around here?"

    old "Sarah frowned. She doubted that was the answer."
    new "Sarah frowned. She doubted that was the answer."

    old "So why do you think you could go about unmolested then?"
    new "So why do you think you could go about unmolested then?"

    old "Sarah thought about it for a moment, then it dawned on her."
    new "Sarah thought about it for a moment, then it dawned on her."

    old "Because I am his..."
    new "Because I am his..."

    old "Your his slave. Your no different in their eyes than the shoes he wears."
    new "Your his slave. Your no different in their eyes than the shoes he wears."

    old "You wouldn't disrespect a man by stealing his shoes. So too, you wouldn't disrespect a man by harming his slave."
    new "You wouldn't disrespect a man by stealing his shoes. So too, you wouldn't disrespect a man by harming his slave."

    old "They don't worry about hurting you. They worry about hurting his pride."
    new "They don't worry about hurting you. They worry about hurting his pride."

    old "And Jaeid is well respected around these parts."
    new "And Jaeid is well respected around these parts."

    old "Sarah's voice had gone quiet. It was slowly dawning on her what she had become."
    new "Sarah's voice had gone quiet. It was slowly dawning on her what she had become."

    old "So if I walk out there..."
    new "So if I walk out there..."

    old "You will be safe, so far as people understand what you are. A slave that belongs to someone."
    new "You will be safe, so far as people understand what you are. A slave that belongs to someone."

    old "But still, this city being what it is..."
    new "But still, this city being what it is..."

    old "The truth is there are men who don't even respect that much. There are still dangers out there."
    new "The truth is there are men who don't even respect that much. There are still dangers out there."

    old "Can I call upon the guards?"
    new "Can I call upon the guards?"

    old "Sure, but this is not Rosanna. The guards are mostly bored warriors who prefer to be gambling and drinking."
    new "Sure, but this is not Rosanna. The guards are mostly bored warriors who prefer to be gambling and drinking."

    old "And the truth is, a slave being used is hardly anything they worry much over."
    new "And the truth is, a slave being used is hardly anything they worry much over."

    old "At most, if they even find the man guilty of it, he would be sentenced to paying Jaeid some coin as an apology."
    new "At most, if they even find the man guilty of it, he would be sentenced to paying Jaeid some coin as an apology."

    old "The idea that if her honour were violated, it would be Jaeid who would be compensated, made Sarah shudder."
    new "The idea that if her honour were violated, it would be Jaeid who would be compensated, made Sarah shudder."

    old "But what honour did she really have, given her current station?"
    new "But what honour did she really have, given her current station?"

    old "Sarah could feel the tears near to her eyes."
    new "Sarah could feel the tears near to her eyes."

    old "Look at her! You're scaring the poor girl."
    new "Look at her! You're scaring the poor girl."

    old "Scaring? I'm just preparing her for the real world."
    new "Scaring? I'm just preparing her for the real world."

    old "Sarah watched as the two argued back and forth."
    new "Sarah watched as the two argued back and forth."

    old "She still struggled to make sense of her own place in this dynamic. This new place."
    new "She still struggled to make sense of her own place in this dynamic. This new place."

    old "Finally, she gathered her courage to speak up."
    new "Finally, she gathered her courage to speak up."

    old "Yes? What is it, Sarah?"
    new "Yes? What is it, Sarah?"

    old "I was wondering if perhaps...there was something to be done about...this?"
    new "I was wondering if perhaps...there was something to be done about...this?"

    old "Sarah gestured at her own naked body."
    new "Sarah gestured at her own naked body."

    old "She had gotten more comfortable with being naked before others than she could have ever believed."
    new "She had gotten more comfortable with being naked before others than she could have ever believed."

    old "Still, she wanted the dignity of some clothes. At least that much."
    new "Still, she wanted the dignity of some clothes. At least that much."

    old "Ooh...yes...I..."
    new "Ooh...yes...I..."

    old "Jaied turned to Jasmine."
    new "Jaied turned to Jasmine."

    old "Do you think if we gave her a tunic it would-"
    new "Do you think if we gave her a tunic it would-"

    old "What are you trying to do?! Get us both killed?"
    new "What are you trying to do?! Get us both killed?"

    old "I just mean, nobody knows that-"
    new "I just mean, nobody knows that-"

    old "They will! Someone saw her through the window. They saw you walk the streets with her. People aren't fools, Jaeid."
    new "They will! Someone saw her through the window. They saw you walk the streets with her. People aren't fools, Jaeid."

    old "They know what she is, and you know the laws."
    new "They know what she is, and you know the laws."

    old "Jasmine looked about the room."
    new "Jasmine looked about the room."

    old "Well...I still have my old uniform from when you first claimed me."
    new "Well...I still have my old uniform from when you first claimed me."

    old "She can have that."
    new "She can have that."

    old "Jaied frowned."
    new "Jaied frowned."

    old "You still have that?"
    new "You still have that?"

    old "Yeah, maybe I thought it would come in handy one day when you proved to be an idiot again."
    new "Yeah, maybe I thought it would come in handy one day when you proved to be an idiot again."

    old "Maybe I was an idiot the day I claimed you."
    new "Maybe I was an idiot the day I claimed you."

    old "Jasmine laughed."
    new "Jasmine laughed."

    old "That much is probably true. I'll go and see about uniform, give me a moment."
    new "That much is probably true. I'll go and see about uniform, give me a moment."

    old "Sarah watched as Jasmine dissapeared from the room, returning only a moment later."
    new "Sarah watched as Jasmine dissapeared from the room, returning only a moment later."

    old "In her hands, a series of strings, a few tiny bracelets and the smallest coverings of cloth."
    new "In her hands, a series of strings, a few tiny bracelets and the smallest coverings of cloth."

    old "What...is that?"
    new "What...is that?"

    old "Clothes."
    new "Clothes."

    old "Those are not...they are barely undergarments, let alone clothes!"
    new "Those are not...they are barely undergarments, let alone clothes!"

    old "Surely you must have something more...decent?"
    new "Surely you must have something more...decent?"

    old "Ooh, trust me, we do. But there are laws."
    new "Ooh, trust me, we do. But there are laws."

    old "Laws?"
    new "Laws?"

    old "You want to to tell her, Jaeid?"
    new "You want to to tell her, Jaeid?"

    old "The laws dictate that a slave must be...easily visible as such."
    new "The laws dictate that a slave must be...easily visible as such."

    old "And in practice that means...well a slave uniform."
    new "And in practice that means...well a slave uniform."

    old "Sarah looked at the clothes that Jasmine held in her hands."
    new "Sarah looked at the clothes that Jasmine held in her hands."

    old "You...want me to wear that?"
    new "You...want me to wear that?"

    old "Looking it, it almost seemed worse than being naked."
    new "Looking it, it almost seemed worse than being naked."

    old "Trust me, if I could give you a tunic, I would, but the laws are strict on this matter..."
    new "Trust me, if I could give you a tunic, I would, but the laws are strict on this matter..."

    old "Sarah took the garment from Jasmine's hands and held it up."
    new "Sarah took the garment from Jasmine's hands and held it up."

    old "She sighed, then committed herself to putting the thing on."
    new "She sighed, then committed herself to putting the thing on."

    old "When she finally had fit herself into it, she looked at herself."
    new "When she finally had fit herself into it, she looked at herself."

    old "If she had worn anything like this in Rosanna, and be caught...it would have been a scandal for the rest of her life."
    new "If she had worn anything like this in Rosanna, and be caught...it would have been a scandal for the rest of her life."

    old "Here...this thing was just part of the ordinary way."
    new "Here...this thing was just part of the ordinary way."

    old "How do I...look?"
    new "How do I...look?"

    old "Jaeid turned his eyes away from her."
    new "Jaeid turned his eyes away from her."

    old "You look the part of a slave. Mister proper here probably can't stand to look at you though."
    new "You look the part of a slave. Mister proper here probably can't stand to look at you though."

    old "Sarah could see Jaeid still kept his gaze averted from her."
    new "Sarah could see Jaeid still kept his gaze averted from her."

    old "Don't worry, he was like that with me too when I first came here."
    new "Don't worry, he was like that with me too when I first came here."

    old "Jasmine! Enough!"
    new "Jasmine! Enough!"

    old "What? It's true. He's more shy than he likes to show."
    new "What? It's true. He's more shy than he likes to show."

    old "But you can wear a tunic now?"
    new "But you can wear a tunic now?"

    old "There are ways to free oneself. Earn the right to stop wearing...well that."
    new "There are ways to free oneself. Earn the right to stop wearing...well that."

    old "Jasmine gestured at Sarah's clothes."
    new "Jasmine gestured at Sarah's clothes."

    old "Can't you just free me then?"
    new "Can't you just free me then?"

    old "No...I fear not."
    new "No...I fear not."

    old "Because the Tribes respect a slave that learns their place. Works to integrate into the Tribes. Become a member by submitting."
    new "Because the Tribes respect a slave that learns their place. Works to integrate into the Tribes. Become a member by submitting."

    old "They allow masters to set their slaves free, but they are no fools."
    new "They allow masters to set their slaves free, but they are no fools."

    old "They deeply believe in the system of slavery, and so anything done to overturn that is looked upon with suspicion."
    new "They deeply believe in the system of slavery, and so anything done to overturn that is looked upon with suspicion."

    old "If Jaeid claimed you one day and set you free the next day, they would know you had never earned your freedom."
    new "If Jaeid claimed you one day and set you free the next day, they would know you had never earned your freedom."

    old "And they would look at Jaeid with suspicion for undermining the institution."
    new "And they would look at Jaeid with suspicion for undermining the institution."

    old "Sarah tried to get used to all these new cultural rules."
    new "Sarah tried to get used to all these new cultural rules."

    old "Also, they would simply never respect him as a man again."
    new "Also, they would simply never respect him as a man again."

    old "Because no proper Tribesman would ever let a girl like you go free without putting half a dozen babies in you."
    new "Because no proper Tribesman would ever let a girl like you go free without putting half a dozen babies in you."

    old "Sarah felt a jolt of panic again."
    new "Sarah felt a jolt of panic again."

    old "Jasmine, stop scaring her."
    new "Jasmine, stop scaring her."

    old "What? I'm not. Are you going to try and tell her they don't go nuts for girls like her?"
    new "What? I'm not. Are you going to try and tell her they don't go nuts for girls like her?"

    old "Sarah could see Jaeid awkwardly fumble his words."
    new "Sarah could see Jaeid awkwardly fumble his words."

    old "To you, all of this must seem exotic. But to them, you're the one that is exotic."
    new "To you, all of this must seem exotic. But to them, you're the one that is exotic."

    old "Just keep your wits about you, is all I'm saying."
    new "Just keep your wits about you, is all I'm saying."

    old "Well, if we're all done with this, how about I show Sarah about?"
    new "Well, if we're all done with this, how about I show Sarah about?"

    old "Is that wise? She would be safer here."
    new "Is that wise? She would be safer here."

    old "Of course she would be."
    new "Of course she would be."

    old "Hell, go buy her a crate and we can lock her up in it and nobody will ever harm her."
    new "Hell, go buy her a crate and we can lock her up in it and nobody will ever harm her."

    old "Jasmine, I-"
    new "Jasmine, I-"

    old "Look, Jaeid, this is her new life. The sooner she gets used to it and learns the rules, the better."
    new "Look, Jaeid, this is her new life. The sooner she gets used to it and learns the rules, the better."

    old "Besides, I need new supplies for my work today, and she can help carry them."
    new "Besides, I need new supplies for my work today, and she can help carry them."

    old "Jasmine! She is not our slave!"
    new "Jasmine! She is not our slave!"

    old "It's okay, Jaeid. If I can be useful...I'd like to be. I think it's right what she says. It will help me learn about this place."
    new "It's okay, Jaeid. If I can be useful...I'd like to be. I think it's right what she says. It will help me learn about this place."

    old "If she ever wanted to have any hope of escaping, she would have to learn the ways of the city."
    new "If she ever wanted to have any hope of escaping, she would have to learn the ways of the city."

    old "The best way was an experienced guide."
    new "The best way was an experienced guide."

    old "Fine, but be careful then."
    new "Fine, but be careful then."

    old "I have business at the palace."
    new "I have business at the palace."

    old "Jasmine nodded, then she grabbed Sarah's hand and began to pull her away."
    new "Jasmine nodded, then she grabbed Sarah's hand and began to pull her away."

    old "Stepping out of the house, the glaring heat of the desert came down on her."
    new "Stepping out of the house, the glaring heat of the desert came down on her."

    old "Sarah could see Jasmine was already walking ahead of her."
    new "Sarah could see Jasmine was already walking ahead of her."

    old "Keep up."
    new "Keep up."

    old "Sarah quickly ran after Jasmine."
    new "Sarah quickly ran after Jasmine."

    old "Catching up to her, she tried to keep with the young woman's swift pace."
    new "Catching up to her, she tried to keep with the young woman's swift pace."

    old "Sorry if I go a bit fast, but I like to walk the market early."
    new "Sorry if I go a bit fast, but I like to walk the market early."

    old "Before long, its going to be more crowded than anything you've ever seen."
    new "Before long, its going to be more crowded than anything you've ever seen."

    old "Better to do your shopping early and be gone befor the rush."
    new "Better to do your shopping early and be gone befor the rush."

    old "Sarah nodded as she tried to keep up with Jasmine."
    new "Sarah nodded as she tried to keep up with Jasmine."

    old "What are we looking for, exactly?"
    new "What are we looking for, exactly?"

    old "Ink. A particular kind, Pale Eclipse, they call it."
    new "Ink. A particular kind, Pale Eclipse, they call it."

    old "Sarah saw a few men looking in her direction. She quickly forced herself to look ahead."
    new "Sarah saw a few men looking in her direction. She quickly forced herself to look ahead."

    old "You better learn to get over that."
    new "You better learn to get over that."

    old "That awkwardness. It might be cute in Rosanna, but here, it just signals weakness. And weakness invites troublemakers."
    new "That awkwardness. It might be cute in Rosanna, but here, it just signals weakness. And weakness invites troublemakers."

    old "So what do I do then?"
    new "So what do I do then?"

    old "Don't even make eye contact with them. You are Jaeid's property, and so by extension, you are beyond them."
    new "Don't even make eye contact with them. You are Jaeid's property, and so by extension, you are beyond them."

    old "Is Jaeid that important?"
    new "Is Jaeid that important?"

    old "Well, compared to the Khan or one of his captains, he isn't much."
    new "Well, compared to the Khan or one of his captains, he isn't much."

    old "But he has the Khan's ear and has proven himself on the battlefield."
    new "But he has the Khan's ear and has proven himself on the battlefield."

    old "For a former slave, he's done quite well for himself."
    new "For a former slave, he's done quite well for himself."

    old "Jasmine gestured towards one of the stalls."
    new "Jasmine gestured towards one of the stalls."

    old "That is one of the Ink merchants, let's go ahead and see if he as what I need."
    new "That is one of the Ink merchants, let's go ahead and see if he as what I need."

    old "You're looking for Pale Eclipse Ink"
    new "You're looking for Pale Eclipse Ink"

    old "That's right. You're a quick study, Sarah. I like that."
    new "That's right. You're a quick study, Sarah. I like that."

    old "Most of the women here, forgive me for saying, but they take to their roles too much."
    new "Most of the women here, forgive me for saying, but they take to their roles too much."

    old "Well I mean that just because you're a slave, doesn't mean you have to act like you're an imbecile."
    new "Well I mean that just because you're a slave, doesn't mean you have to act like you're an imbecile."

    old "They do?"
    new "They do?"

    old "Well, it's hardly their fault."
    new "Well, it's hardly their fault."

    old "The Tribesmen are not a complicated people. They like a pretty girl for...well, the obvious reasons."
    new "The Tribesmen are not a complicated people. They like a pretty girl for...well, the obvious reasons."

    old "So the slaves, well they tend to become like pets. They behave in a way that their masters want them to."
    new "So the slaves, well they tend to become like pets. They behave in a way that their masters want them to."

    old "Because if they do what their masters want, their masters will be nice to them."
    new "Because if they do what their masters want, their masters will be nice to them."

    old "But if they're slaves for too long they become exhausting. They don't use their brains for years on end, so they all but end up losing them."
    new "But if they're slaves for too long they become exhausting. They don't use their brains for years on end, so they all but end up losing them."

    old "She shuddered at the idea of having to behave like a simpleton for years on end."
    new "She shuddered at the idea of having to behave like a simpleton for years on end."

    old "You're looking for White Moonfall Ink"
    new "You're looking for White Moonfall Ink"

    old "What are you talking about? Do you even listen when I talk?"
    new "What are you talking about? Do you even listen when I talk?"

    old "You're looking for Faded Stars Ink"
    new "You're looking for Faded Stars Ink"

    old "Together, they walked to the ink merchant."
    new "Together, they walked to the ink merchant."

    old "Sarah looked at all the vials, filled with what seemed to be identical black liquids."
    new "Sarah looked at all the vials, filled with what seemed to be identical black liquids."

    old "It's...all ink."
    new "It's...all ink."

    old "Well, yeah. It is an ink merchant, after all."
    new "Well, yeah. It is an ink merchant, after all."

    old "But I mean...what difference does it make?"
    new "But I mean...what difference does it make?"

    old "Jasmine pointed at a few vials."
    new "Jasmine pointed at a few vials."

    old "Colour wise, there are some subtle differences."
    new "Colour wise, there are some subtle differences."

    old "Those are typical black, but those others turn a dark purple after a few days."
    new "Those are typical black, but those others turn a dark purple after a few days."

    old "She pointed out the next few."
    new "She pointed out the next few."

    old "That there is Pale Eclips, what I use for my cartography."
    new "That there is Pale Eclips, what I use for my cartography."

    old "Why? If it's all black anyway?"
    new "Why? If it's all black anyway?"

    old "It binds the easiest with the paper I use."
    new "It binds the easiest with the paper I use."

    old "The maps I make are mostly used for war campaigns, so they are a tougher parchment made from a particular tree from this region."
    new "The maps I make are mostly used for war campaigns, so they are a tougher parchment made from a particular tree from this region."

    old "Regular ink doesn't bind well, the maps get faded, and before you know it the army is marching in the wrong direction."
    new "Regular ink doesn't bind well, the maps get faded, and before you know it the army is marching in the wrong direction."

    old "One time I sold a map that was a bit poorer in quality."
    new "One time I sold a map that was a bit poorer in quality."

    old "They ended up looting the wrong city near one of the borders."
    new "They ended up looting the wrong city near one of the borders."

    old "Can you imagine?"
    new "Can you imagine?"

    old "Your whole family killed. Your home burned. Turned into a slave."
    new "Your whole family killed. Your home burned. Turned into a slave."

    old "All because some girl you never met forgot to use the proper ink and sold a faded map to a raiding party."
    new "All because some girl you never met forgot to use the proper ink and sold a faded map to a raiding party."

    old "Jasmine laughed to herself as she said it."
    new "Jasmine laughed to herself as she said it."

    old "That's horrible."
    new "That's horrible."

    old "Sarah saw Jasmine's face suddenly drop."
    new "Sarah saw Jasmine's face suddenly drop."

    old "I can't believe you would laugh at something like that."
    new "I can't believe you would laugh at something like that."

    old "Jasmine was quiet for a brief moment."
    new "Jasmine was quiet for a brief moment."

    old "Out of all the words Sarah had expected, she didn't expect that one."
    new "Out of all the words Sarah had expected, she didn't expect that one."

    old "I forget myself sometimes. With Jaeid, I can joke because he understands where I come from."
    new "I forget myself sometimes. With Jaeid, I can joke because he understands where I come from."

    old "I have to get used to you being here now."
    new "I have to get used to you being here now."

    old "I laugh about all this because...well the alternative is that I cry about it all day, and I can't do that."
    new "I laugh about all this because...well the alternative is that I cry about it all day, and I can't do that."

    old "Sarah saw Jasmine's eyes turning away from her."
    new "Sarah saw Jasmine's eyes turning away from her."

    old "Sorry if I was too harsh...I just, this is all still new to me. Laughing about it seems..."
    new "Sorry if I was too harsh...I just, this is all still new to me. Laughing about it seems..."

